message.content: cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. The paper deals with Visual Question Answering, which is a task that involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a model-agnostic framework that exploits cycle consistency, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence research, suggesting that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
